Is the old woman on the bicycle still alive?
Yes, she jumped right back up.
utterances.transcript_with_note: Yes, she jumped right back up. (Ross opens his eyes.)

utterances.transcript: Oh my God, Phoebe, slow down!
Do you wanna get to Rachel in time?
Yes, but I don't wanna die in your cab!
You should have thought of that before you got in!
utterances.transcript_with_note: You should have thought of that before you got in! (They drive up to a toll-booth.)

utterances.transcript: Toll-booth.
What?
Toll-booth! Four bucks. There are quarters in the glove compartment.
utterances.transcript_with_note: (screaming) Toll-booth! Four bucks. There are quarters in the glove compartment. (Ross tries to open a plastic bag filled with quarters, but he's quite slow.)

utterances.transcript: Hurry!
Okay!
Okay.
utterances.transcript_with_note: Okay. (Phoebe tries to throw some quarters out the window, but she has forgotten to open the window, and she and Ross scream.)

utterances.transcript: Damn, that window is clean.

utterances.transcript_with_note: [Scene: Joey's apartment. Joey is still looking for the birds.]

utterances.transcript: Quack, quack, tweet, tweet, quack, quack, tweet, tweet, quack, quack, tweet, tweet, quack, quack, tweet, tweet, quack, tweet, quack...
utterances.transcript_with_note: Quack, quack, tweet, tweet, quack, quack, tweet, tweet, quack, quack, tweet, tweet, quack, quack, tweet, tweet, quack, tweet, quack... (Monica and Chandler enter.)

utterances.transcript: We were wondering what was taking so long with the gift, but now we understand you were doing this.
Okay, I wanted to surprise you, but for your house-warming gift, I got you a baby-chick and a baby-duck!
utterances.transcript_with_note: Okay, I wanted to surprise you, but for your house-warming gift, I got you a baby-chick and a baby-duck! (Chandler grins, while Monica is less enthusiastic.)

utterances.transcript: Really? You got us a chick and a duck?
Oh, great! Just what you want for a new house with infants. Bird feces.
Yeah, yeah, they must have jumped off the table, 'cause now they're gone!
Oh, don't worry, we'll find them.
Actually, I'm gonna go check on the twins.
Alright.
utterances.transcript_with_note: Alright. (Monica turns around and is about to leave when she steps on something.)

utterances.transcript: Oh God! What did I just step on?
Oh!
It's okay, it's just an egg roll.
Oh..
You stepped on my egg roll?
I'm sorry, I didn't know to look for Chinese food on the floor.
Just put it on a plate and leave.
utterances.transcript_with_note: Just put it on a plate and leave. (She does so.)

utterances.transcript: Okay, let's find these birds.
Alright.
utterances.transcript_with_note: Alright. (Suddenly, they hear the birds.)

utterances.transcript: Wait, wait. Do you hear that?
utterances.transcript_with_note: Wait, wait. Do you hear that? (They realise that the birds are in the foosball table.)

utterances.transcript: Oh! They're in the table!
Well, that can't be good!
We gotta get them out of there!
How?
Oh, oh! Maybe we can lure them out. You know any birdcalls?
Oh, tons, I'm quite the woodsman.
Well, maybe we can just tip the table a little.
Joey, wait! The ball!
Oh!
utterances.transcript_with_note: Oh! (The ball rolls into one of the goals, and Chandler and Joey listen in horror as the ball makes its way inside the table. Finally, they can hear the birds again.)

utterances.transcript: Oh God! So what do we do?
I don't know. Maybe we can open this up somehow.
Okay.
No... It's all glued together.
Does that mean we have to bust it open?
I don't know. Maybe.
Oh my God!
I know! It's.. It's the foosball table.

All right, you know what? We don't have a choice. It's like I would have said in that sci-fi movie if I'd gotten the part. "Those are our men in there, we have to get them out! Even if I have to sacrifice the most important thing in my life; my time-machine."
Did that movie ever get made?
It did not.

utterances.transcript_with_note: [Scene: The airport. Ross and Phoebe run in.]

utterances.transcript: Ross, where are you going?
To talk to Rachel, isn't that why we took a ride in the death-cab?
What? What are you just gonna walk up to her at the gate? Have you never chased anyone through the airport before?
Not since my cop-show got cancelled.
You have to get a ticket to get past security.
What? We're never gonna make it!
Not with that attitude! Now, haul ass!
utterances.transcript_with_note: Not with that attitude! Now, haul ass! (They run to the ticket counter, but they get stuck behind a group of old people who are walking very slowly.)

utterances.transcript: Okay, if you could all walk slower, that'd be great.

plots: Phoebe and Ross chase Rachel in Phoebe 's taxi to catch Rachel at the airport before Rachel takes off , but they end up at the wrong airport .
Rachel tells Ross that Ross needs a ticket to get pasts security .
